
[Charlottesville, 31? May 1781. JHD, May 1781, 1828 edn., p. 7 (31 May): The Speaker laid before the House a letter from the Governor, enclosing one from Baron Steuben, with a representation of the present state of the Virginia line; which was read and ordered to be [50] referred to the committee of the whole House on the state of the Commonwealth. TJs letter has not been found; the one from Baron Steuben is his to TJ of 28 May, which enclosed the state of the Virginia line, printed above.]
